                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scope="sole" xml:id="hand-1">
                                <p>The main text was copied in a <term type="script">mixed
                                        minuscule</term> script, slanting slightly to the right, in
                                    brown ink. There is moderate variation in letter size.</p>
                                <p>Syllabic abbreviations appear throughout the line, while
                                    superscript word endings appear only at the end of lines.
                                    Breathings are round, and mute <hi rend="italic">iota</hi> is
                                    absent or subscript. There is decorative use of the double dot,
                                    and accentuation of all lengths of <foreign xml:lang="la">nomina
                                        sacra</foreign>.</p>
                                <p>Distinctive letter-forms include minuscule <hi rend="italic">eta</hi> with a broad space after the initial ascender
                                    (e.g. <locus from="1r" to="1r">recto, col. b, lines 2,
                                        14</locus>) and a large minuscule <hi rend="italic">upsilon</hi> curved inwards at the top (e.g. <locus from="1v" to="1v">verso, col. a, lines 9, 11</locus>).</p>
                                <p>Punctuation used includes the upper point, lower and middle
                                    commas and full stop.</p>
                                <p>Headings and <hi rend="italic">eirmoi</hi> have been copied in
                                    the same style in red ink.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>

                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="colInit">Lections begin with simple minor initials in
                                red ink.</decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>

